{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I will love you, O LORD, my strength."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The LORD is my rock and my fortress and my deliverer,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "my God, my strength, in whom I will trust;",
          "speaker": "David"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "my shield and the horn of my salvation, my stronghold."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "my strength: Heb. my rock"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I will call upon the LORD, who is worthy to be praised;"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "So shall I be saved from my enemies.",
          "speaker": "David"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 4,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The pangs of death surrounded me,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and the floods of ungodly men made me afraid."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "ungodly men: Heb. Belial"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 5,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sorrows of Sheol surrounded me;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "the snares of death confronted me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "sorrows: or, cords"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "In my distress I called upon the LORD,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "and cried out to my God;",
          "speaker": "David"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He heard my voice from His temple,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and my cry came before Him, even to His ears."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 7,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then the earth shook and trembled;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "the foundations of the hills also quaked and were shaken,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "because He was angry."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 8,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Smoke went up from His nostrils,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and devouring fire from His mouth;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "coals were kindled by it."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "out of his nostrils: Heb. by his, etc"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 9,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He bowed the heavens also, and came down"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "with darkness under His feet."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 10,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And He rode upon a cherub, and flew;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He flew upon the wings of the wind."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 11,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He made darkness His secret place;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "His canopy around Him was dark waters"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and thick clouds of the skies."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 12,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "From the brightness before Him,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "His thick clouds passed with hailstones and coals of fire."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 13,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The LORD thundered from heaven,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and the Most High uttered His voice,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "hailstones and coals of fire."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 14,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He sent out His arrows and scattered the foe,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "lightnings in abundance, and He vanquished them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then the channels of the sea were seen,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "the foundations of the world were uncovered"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "at Your rebuke, O LORD,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "at the blast of the breath of Your nostrils."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He sent from above, He took me;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He drew me out of many waters."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "many: or, great"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 17,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He delivered me from my strong enemy,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "from those who hated me;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "for they were too strong for me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 18,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They confronted me in the day of my calamity,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "but the LORD was my support."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 19,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He also brought me out into a broad place;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He delivered me because He delighted in me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 20,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The LORD rewarded me according to my righteousness;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "according to the cleanness of my hands He has recompensed me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For I have kept the ways of the LORD,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and have not wickedly departed from my God."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For all His judgments were before me,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and I did not put away His statutes from me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 23,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I was also blameless before Him,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and I kept myself from my iniquity."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "before: Heb. with"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Therefore the LORD has recompensed me according to my righteousness,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "according to the cleanness of my hands in His sight."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "in…: Heb. before his eyes"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 25,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "With the merciful You will show Yourself merciful;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "with the blameless man You will show Yourself blameless;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 26,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "With the pure You will show Yourself pure;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and with the devious You will show Yourself shrewd."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "shew thyself froward: or, wrestle"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 27,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For You will save the humble people,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "but will bring down haughty looks."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 28,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For You will light my lamp;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "the LORD my God will enlighten my darkness."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "candle: or, lamp"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 29,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For by You I can run against a troop,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "by my God I can leap over a wall."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "run…: or, broken"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 30,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "As for God, His way is perfect;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "the word of the LORD is proven;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He is a shield to all who trust in Him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "tried: or, refined"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 31,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For who is God, except the LORD?"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And who is a rock, except our God?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 32,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "It is God who arms me with strength,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and makes my way perfect."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 33,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He makes my feet like the feet of deer,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and sets me on my high places."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 34,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He teaches my hands to make war,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "so that my arms can bend a bow of bronze."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 35,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You have also given me the shield of Your salvation;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Your right hand has held me up,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Your gentleness has made me great."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "thy gentleness…: or, with thy meekness thou hast multiplied me"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 36,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You enlarged my path under me,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "so my feet did not slip."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "my feet: Heb. mine ankles"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 37,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I have pursued my enemies and overtaken them;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "neither did I turn back again till they were destroyed."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 38,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I have wounded them so that they could not rise;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "they have fallen under my feet."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 39,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For You have armed me with strength for the battle;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You have subdued under me those who rose up against me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "subdued: Heb. caused to bow"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 40,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You have also given me the necks of my enemies,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "so that I destroyed those who hated me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 41,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They cried out, but there was none to save;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "even to the LORD, but He did not answer them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 42,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then I beat them as fine as the dust before the wind;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I cast them out like dirt in the streets."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 43,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You have delivered me from the strivings of the people;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You have made me the head of the nations;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A people I have not known shall serve me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 44,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "As soon as they hear of me they obey me;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "the foreigners submit to me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "As soon…: Heb. At the hearing of the ear",
        "submit…: or, yield feigned obedience",
        "strangers: Heb. sons of the stranger"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 45,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The foreigners fade away,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and come frightened from their hideouts."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "strangers: Heb. sons of the stranger"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 46,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The LORD lives! Blessed be my rock!"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Let the God of my salvation be exalted."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 47,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "It is God who avenges me,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and subdues the people under me;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "avengeth: Heb. giveth avengements for",
        "subdueth: or, destroyeth"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 48,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He delivers me from my enemies."
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You also lift me up above those who rise against me;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You have delivered me from the violent man."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "violent…: Heb. man of violence"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 49,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Therefore I will give thanks to You, O LORD, among the Gentiles,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and sing praises to Your name."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        "give…: or, confess"
      ],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 50,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Great deliverance gives He to His king,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and shows mercy to His anointed,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "to David and his descendants forevermore."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    }
  ]
}